A writable key path from parent state to a property containing child","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"presentation state."}]}],"name":"toPresentationState"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A case path from parent action to a case containing child actions.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"toPresentationAction"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A reducer that will be invoked with child actions against presented child","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"state.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"destination"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The fileID.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"fileID"},{"name":"filePath","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The filePath.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"line","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The line."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"column","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The column.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"return-value","level":2,"text":"Return Value","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A reducer that combines the child reducer with the parent reducer."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This version of ","type":"text"},{"code":"ifLet","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" requires the usage of the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Presents()"},{"text":" macro and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type in your feature’s domain."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, if a parent feature holds onto a piece of optional child state, then it can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"perform its core logic "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"and"}]},{"type":"text","text":" the child’s logic by using the "},{"code":"ifLet","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" operator:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@Reducer","struct Parent {","  @ObservableState","  struct State {","    @Presents var child: Child.State?","    \/\/ ...","  }","  enum Action {","    case child(PresentationAction<Child.Action>)","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  var body: some ReducerOf<Self> {","    Reduce { state, action in","      \/\/ Core logic for parent feature","    }","    .ifLet(\\.$child, action: \\.child) {","      Child()","    }","  }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ifLet"},{"text":" operator does a number of things to make integrating parent and child features","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ergonomic and enforce correctness:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It forces a specific order of operations for the child and parent features:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction\/dismiss","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" action is sent, it runs the parent feature"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"before the child state is ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"’d out. This gives the parent feature an opportunity to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"inspect the child state one last time before the state is cleared."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction\/presented(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" action is sent it runs the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"child first, and then the parent. If the order was reversed, then it would be possible"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the parent feature to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" out the child state, in which case the child feature"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"would not be able to react to that action. That can cause subtle bugs.","type":"text"}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It automatically cancels all child effects when it detects the child’s state is "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’d"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"out.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Automatically ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"s out child state when an action is sent for alerts and confirmation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"dialogs.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It gives the child feature access to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/DismissEffect","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" dependency, which allows the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"child feature to dismiss itself without communicating with the parent."}]}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope\/ifLet(_:action:destination:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-2u5gv","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArc